PrecisAcceptance of an instrument entitled "DOCUMENT OF ABSOLUTE SURRENDER", duly approved by the BUCTOUCHE BAND OF INDIANS at a referendum held on February 9, 1993, whereby the band surrenders all rights and interests, including mines and minerals, with respect to some 106.37 hectares (263 acres) of land situated on The Buctouche Indian Reserve No. 16, in the Province of New Brunswick.
